OL,3,CThe economy is turning a corner - but
OL,4,Cvery slowly
OL,6,FThe UK has been hit by a series of
OL,7,Feconomic shocks in recent years, but
OL,8,Four economic problems pre-date the
OL,9,Fpandemic, the invasion of Ukraine, and
OL,10,FBrexit.
OL,12,FThe truth is the UK has been stuck in
OL,13,Fa low growth rut since 2008 and, as a
OL,14,Fresult, wages have barely grown.
OL,16,FBetween 1992 and 2007 - under John
OL,17,FMajor and Tony Blair - Gross Domestic
OL,18,FProduct (GDP) per person in the UK
OL,19,Feconomy increased by 45.9%.
