OL,3,CThe economy is turning a corner - but
OL,4,Cvery slowly
OL,6,FIn the last 15 years since - Gordon
OL,7,FBrown, David Cameron, Theresa May,
OL,8,FBoris Johnson, Liz Truss and Rishi
OL,9,FSunak - it has grown by just 4.3%.
OL,11,FHad the economy continued on its pre-
OL,12,F2008 trend, the Resolution Foundation
OL,13,Fcalculates that the average worker
OL,14,Fwould be #14,000 a year better off.
OL,16,FSlow growth is a serious problem. The
OL,17,FUK is not the only wealthy country to
OL,18,Fexperience "stagnation" but our strain
OL,19,Flooks particularly virulent.
